---
import CaseStudy from '../../layouts/CaseStudy.astro';
---
<CaseStudy slug="ark">
  <Fragment slot="header">
    <div class="cs-hero">[Ark of the Covenant — tour and album artwork]</div>
    <div class="cs-tags"><span class="cs-tag">Brand</span><span class="cs-tag">GTM</span><span class="cs-tag">Music</span><span class="cs-tag">Independent</span></div>
    <div class="cs-title">Ark of the Covenant — Independent artist brand built from zero</div>
    <div class="cs-subtitle">Eight years founding and operating an independent music project. 350+ live shows, 2 distribution deals, 20K+ followers, 100K+ streams, and a Mesa/Boogie endorsement — all self-built across brand, booking, production, and audience.</div>
    <div class="cs-meta-card">
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Project</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Ark of the Covenant</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Duration</div><div class="cs-meta-value">2008 – 2016</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Role</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Founder / Drummer</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Industry</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Music · Independent</div></div>
    </div>
  </Fragment>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="stat-strip">
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">350+</div><div class="stat-label">Live shows played</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">20K+</div><div class="stat-label">Followers built organically</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">100K+</div><div class="stat-label">Streams across platforms</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Context · Action · Result</div>
    <div class="car-grid">
      <div class="car-sidebar">
        <div class="car-step active" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-ark-1')"><div class="car-step-label">01 · Context</div><div class="car-step-title">The situation</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-ark-2')"><div class="car-step-label">02 · Action</div><div class="car-step-title">What I built</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-ark-3')"><div class="car-step-label">03 · Result</div><div class="car-step-title">What it produced</div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div id="car-ark-1" class="car-content">
          <div class="car-content-label">01 · Context</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">An independent music project with no label, no budget, and no existing audience.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Ark of the Covenant started with no label infrastructure, no marketing budget, and no pre-existing audience. Brand identity, booking, production, press, merch, and audience development all had to be built from scratch — in an era when streaming was still reshaping how independent artists reached listeners.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-ark-2" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">02 · Action</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">Owned every layer of the project end-to-end.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Built the brand from the inside out — identity, artwork, merch, and visual system. Ran booking and tour planning for 350+ live shows. Negotiated two distribution deals and secured a Mesa/Boogie drumhead endorsement. Produced press, social, and audience-building across every channel available.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-ark-3" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">03 · Result</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">350+ shows. 20K+ followers. 100K+ streams. Two distribution deals.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Over eight years, played 350+ live shows, grew to 20K+ followers, landed 100K+ streams across platforms, and released material through two distribution partners. The project became the foundation for the brand-building instincts that carry through every engagement at THIS.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</CaseStudy>
